  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Playgrounds: a tool to increase access to ECD education in Uganda&apos;s refugee settlements</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A project to install community-designed playgrounds and deliver training for teachers in interactive teaching in 59 ECD centres in refugee-hosting areas of Uganda, over 36 months, improving the quality of ECD provision for 28,323 enrolled children, and increasing enrolment by 50% (14,161 children), through children engaging with playgrounds. 1,475 adults will be trained (295 teachers, 1,180 parents) in interactive teaching and play&apos;s importance, and will be encouraged to share knowledge with others.</narrative>
  </description>
